String Compression 

Given a string S, compress the string by its character and its count as specified in the sample input and output.

Boundary Condition:
1<= Length of S <= 10000

Input Format:
The first line contains the string S.

Output Format:
The first line contains the compressed string format.

Sample Input/Output 1:
Input:
aaabbbbccÂ 

Output:
a3b4c2

Sample Input/Output 2:
Input:
abc

Output:
a1b1c1



#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#include<string.h>
int main()
{
    char a[10000],t;
    int i,j,n;
    scanf("%s",a);
    n=strlen(a);
    for(i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        j=1;
        t=a[i];
        while(a[i]==a[i+1])
        {
            t=a[i];
            j+=1;
            i++;
        }
        printf("%c%d",t,j);
    }
}
